    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "A380\nAVIATION\nPOST\nS AUGUST 2008\nAIRBUS A380\nAUSTRALIA 2",
      "AVIATION\nIn 2008 pantas takes delivery of its first Airbus A380-841, the world's largest airliner. Pantas has 20 A380s on order,\nwith a further four options. The fantas A380 will seat 450 passengers on its two main decks, weigh in at a maximum\n560 tonnes and can cruise at Mach 0.85 (1,015 km/h) for 9,200 nm (17,000 km). Designed with cutting-edge materials\nand technologies, the A380 is also quieter and more fuel-efficient than previous airliners. The interiors of pantas A380s\nare designed by world-renowned Australian industrial designer Marc Newson, with the cabin environment combining\nthe latest innovations to enhance comfort and provide access to SMS, telephone and a wide range of entertainment\noptions. As with all international aircraft today, the A380 also carries international airmail.\nStamp illustration: Jamie Tufrey\nStamp design: Jonathan Chong\nStamp background images: Airbus\nCover design: Jo Muré, Australia Post Design Studio\nBackground images: © PhotoDisc Library; © 2008 Jupiterimages Corporation\n12154/15,000\nQANTAS\nRRP $9.95\nwww.auspost.com.au/stamps\n• POST\n9 312650 360030"
    ],
